name: Night on Disco Mountain
comments: Orchestral disco adaptation for the 1977 motion picture "Saturday Night Fever". The arrangement was released as part of the film's best-selling soundtrack. "Night on Disco Mountain" is based on the first portion of Mussorgsky's composition complementing the composer's unusual selection of instruments with wah-wah electric guitar solo, synthesized bells, a constantly throbbing electric bass, hi-hat, snare drum and a variety of exotic bongos and percussion instruments", "various studio sound effects", and "an otherworldly synthesized chorus"
